            <span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Calibri"> <strong> Instructions for Submitting Camera-Ready Copy </strong></span> <br /><br />

            <b>Camera-ready copy is due on June 1, 2010</b>. <br /><br />
		
The authors of accepted papers are required to submit the following items in a zip, tar or tar.gz file: <br /><br />
<ol>
<li>Completed and signed <a href="./copyrightlncs.pdf">copyright form</a>. One author may sign on behalf of all of the other authors of a particular paper. <br /><br />
<li>Source files. <br />
    <ul>
    <li>Final pdf file of your paper. <br />
    <li>LaTeX files with all the associated style files, special fonts and eps or bib files. <br />
    <li>A readme.txt file showing the name and email address of the corresponding author. <br />
    <li>Final DVI file (for papers prepared using LaTeX/TeX) <br />
    <li>RTF files (for word-processing systems other than LaTeX/TeX) <br /><br />
    </ul>
</ol>

Each full length submission can have at most 10 pages, while each short submission can have at most 5 pages. Additional pages are charged at least $150 per page. Springer provides you with a complete integrated LATEX document class (llncs.cls) for multi-author books such as those in the <a href="http://www.springer.com/lncs/">LNCS series</a>. Papers not complying with the LNCS style will be reformatted. This can lead to an increase in the overall number of pages. <br /><br />

Please submit your final materials via EasyChair Conference System by following the link below: <br />
<a href="http://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=wasa2010">http://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=wasa2010.</a>
<br />
After following the above link, click on the Proceedings tab and then follow the link to the paper. The revised paper can be submitted by clicking on the "submit new version" link.
<br /><br />

The submission deadline for the camera-ready copy of your paper is <b>June 1, 2010</b>. Please note that this is a firm deadline, and failing to submit your final version by then may result in its withdrawal from the conference program. Questions about the submission process should be directed to Program Chairs.

